// Generated from registry: congruenceTransformationProofMethod
// showTemplate, showExample
// title: 'Congruence — Transformation Proof Method'
static congruenceTransformationProofMethodSvg = `<?xml version="1.0" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE svg PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD SVG 20010904//EN"
 "http://www.w3.org/TR/2001/REC-SVG-20010904/DTD/svg10.dtd">
<svg version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
 width="800" height="600" viewBox="0 0 800 600"
 preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
<metadata>Congruence Transformation Proof Method</metadata>
<g fill="none" stroke="#000000">

<!-- Title -->
<text x="400" y="35" font-family="Arial" font-size="20" fill="#000000" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="bold">Congruence — Transformation Proof Method</text>
<text x="400" y="58" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#555555" text-anchor="middle">Prove congruence by explicitly describing an isometry that maps one shape to the other</text>

<!-- TEMPLATE -->
<text x="400" y="82" font-family="Arial" font-size="14" fill="#000000" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="bold">Proof Template</text>

<rect x="30" y="90" width="740" height="198" fill="#F5F5F5" stroke="#000000" stroke-width="2" rx="6"/>

<text x="50" y="113" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">Given:</text>
<text x="130" y="113" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">State the two shapes (e.g. △ABC and △DEF) and any given information</text>

<text x="50" y="135" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">Prove:</text>
<text x="130" y="135" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">△ABC ≅ △DEF</text>

<text x="50" y="158" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">Proof:</text>

<text x="65" y="178" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">1.  Identify the isometry:  "[Translation / Rotation / Reflection / Glide] T such that...</text>
<text x="65" y="198" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">2.  Specify it fully:  e.g. "Rotation of 90° CCW about point O(2,3)" or "Reflection over y = x"</text>
<text x="65" y="218" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">3.  Show it maps vertices:  T(A) = D,  T(B) = E,  T(C) = F  (verify algebraically)</text>
<text x="65" y="238" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">4.  Conclude:  "Since isometry T maps △ABC exactly onto △DEF, △ABC ≅ △DEF.  □"</text>
<text x="65" y="258" font-family="Arial" font-size="11" fill="#555555">     [Note: Isometries preserve all distances and angles, so the shapes must be congruent.]</text>
<text x="65" y="277" font-family="Arial" font-size="11" fill="#555555">     [You do NOT need to verify sides/angles separately once the isometry is established.]</text>

<!-- WORKED EXAMPLE -->
<text x="400" y="308" font-family="Arial" font-size="14" fill="#000000" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="bold">Worked Example</text>

<rect x="30" y="316" width="740" height="225" fill="#FAFAFA" stroke="#AAAAAA" stroke-width="1.5" rx="6"/>

<text x="50" y="338" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">Given:</text>
<text x="130" y="338" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">A(1,1), B(4,1), C(1,5)  and  D(−1,1), E(−4,1), F(−1,5)</text>

<text x="50" y="358" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">Prove:</text>
<text x="130" y="358" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">△ABC ≅ △DEF</text>

<text x="50" y="380" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">Proof:</text>
<text x="65" y="400" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">1.  Consider the reflection S over the y-axis: S(x, y) = (−x, y)</text>
<text x="65" y="420" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">2.  This is fully specified: reflection over the line x = 0 (the y-axis)</text>
<text x="65" y="440" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">3.  Verify vertex images:</text>
<text x="100" y="458" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">S(A) = S(1,1) = (−1,1) = D  ✓</text>
<text x="100" y="476" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">S(B) = S(4,1) = (−4,1) = E  ✓</text>
<text x="100" y="494" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000">S(C) = S(1,5) = (−1,5) = F  ✓</text>
<text x="65" y="514" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">4.  Conclusion: Reflection S over the y-axis maps △ABC exactly onto △DEF.</text>
<text x="65" y="532" font-family="Arial" font-size="12" fill="#000000" font-weight="bold">    Since reflections are isometries, △ABC ≅ △DEF.  □</text>

<text x="400" y="565" font-family="Arial" font-size="11" fill="#555555" text-anchor="middle">Key insight: You only need ONE isometry. You don't need to verify all 6 measurements separately.</text>
<text x="400" y="582" font-family="Arial" font-size="11" fill="#555555" text-anchor="middle">The power of the transformation approach: prove congruence in 4 steps instead of checking each side/angle.</text>

</g>
</svg>`;

